WEBVTT

00:01.209 --> 00:02.710
[♪♪♪]

00:02.877 --> 00:03.919
Good morning, Timmy.

00:04.087 --> 00:06.047
Oh, a very good morning
to you as well.

00:06.214 --> 00:08.299
Do you know
if this coffee is fresh?

00:08.466 --> 00:10.510
If it were any fresher,
you'd have to slap it, ha.

00:10.676 --> 00:11.677
[CHUCKLES]

00:13.138 --> 00:14.930
-That's funny, heh.
-Indeed.

00:15.515 --> 00:17.892
Anyway, guess I'll see you around.

00:18.059 --> 00:20.936
Yes.
And I wish you a peaceful Tuesday.

00:21.104 --> 00:23.731
-Peaceful?
-To offset the influence of Mars...

00:23.898 --> 00:26.567
...the god of war,
for whom Tuesday is named.

00:27.610 --> 00:30.488
-Huh. How about that?
-Heh.

00:33.824 --> 00:38.371
Wow. You hit her with the origin of
Tuesday and she's still not naked?

00:39.164 --> 00:40.206
Oh, you're here.

00:40.373 --> 00:43.793
Clearly the shuttle to and from hell
is back up and running.

00:44.460 --> 00:46.254
Rough way to treat your mentor.

00:46.421 --> 00:48.256
-Gum?
-No thanks.

00:48.423 --> 00:50.300
No, I mean, gum.

00:51.509 --> 00:54.970
So, uh, you likey the new girl.

00:55.138 --> 00:56.931
What would make you say that, sir?

00:57.098 --> 00:59.809
Well, please, your goggles are all
fogged up...

00:59.975 --> 01:01.352
...and you were smiling so big...

01:01.519 --> 01:04.314
...you looked like
the Cleveland Indians' mascot.

01:06.357 --> 01:10.695
Now then, I do admit
to being quite taken by Allison.

01:10.861 --> 01:13.156
She has a certain something
I can't quite put my finger on.

01:13.323 --> 01:15.991
Ah, she's not gonna let you put
your finger on it...

01:16.159 --> 01:19.204
...if you keep the days of the week
fun facts coming.

01:19.370 --> 01:23.791
Sir, not every romantic interaction
begins with, "You're not a cop, are you?"

01:23.958 --> 01:25.335
RUSSELL:
Hmm.

01:25.793 --> 01:27.795
-As your mentor--
-You're not my mentor.

01:27.962 --> 01:30.215
As your mentor...

01:30.381 --> 01:32.383
...if you want to bag Allison...

01:32.550 --> 01:36.387
...you gotta step into it a little bit,
you know? Notch up the offensive.

01:36.554 --> 01:38.806
I'm not trying to bag Allison, sir.

01:38.973 --> 01:41.726
I'm trying to lay the groundwork
for a meaningful relationship.

01:41.892 --> 01:44.812
[IN UNISON]
Groundwork's all you'll be laying.

01:45.771 --> 01:47.106
-Whatever.
-Good one.

01:47.273 --> 01:50.693
I know chicks like this,
they're all librarian on the outside.

01:50.860 --> 01:53.654
Inside's a sexy vixen waiting
for you to bust her out.

01:53.821 --> 01:54.989
Save your breath, sir.

01:55.156 --> 01:59.577
I'd much sooner take romantic advice
from Mr. Eldrick "Tiger" Woods.

02:00.661 --> 02:03.748
-Ouch.
-If I've offended you, I apologize.

02:03.914 --> 02:06.501
Which might in fact be an opening
for you to apologize...

02:06.667 --> 02:08.711
...for all your offensive comments
aimed at me.

02:08.878 --> 02:10.713
Hmm? No? Didn't think so.

02:18.763 --> 02:20.014
Ha-ha!

02:20.181 --> 02:21.307
What are you doing
at Timmy's computer?

02:21.474 --> 02:24.435
I'm sending an email
to that new chick from Timmy.

02:24.852 --> 02:27.021
But Timmy's not here.

02:28.606 --> 02:31.526
Has anyone ever successfully
explained something to you?

02:32.735 --> 02:33.986
Lots of times.

02:34.737 --> 02:37.240
Great.
Okay, I'm sending it as Timmy...

02:37.407 --> 02:39.409
...because he doesn't know
how to close the deal.

02:39.575 --> 02:41.411
-As his mentor--
-Uh, you're not his mentor.

02:41.577 --> 02:44.455
I'm his mentor, all right?

02:45.206 --> 02:48.209
I'm giving him
a little poetic assistance.

02:48.376 --> 02:53.172
"And lick the vanilla icing
off your sweet rack"?

02:53.964 --> 02:56.008
I wanted to go romantic.

02:57.302 --> 02:59.094
[SEÑOR HAPPY'S
"HOW MANY WAYS" PLAYING]

02:59.262 --> 03:02.640
♪ How many ways
To say I love you ♪

03:04.225 --> 03:08.771
♪ How many ways to say
That I'm not scared ♪

03:08.938 --> 03:13.901
♪ When you're by my side
There is no denying ♪

03:14.068 --> 03:17.613
♪ I can't wait for me and you ♪♪

03:21.826 --> 03:23.828
[♪♪♪]

03:25.079 --> 03:26.539
-Oh, jeez.
-Mm.

03:26.706 --> 03:27.790
[CROWD CHEERING ON TV]

03:27.957 --> 03:30.167
Oh, by the way,
I found my other rollerblade...

03:30.335 --> 03:32.920
...so you can disregard my email.

03:35.381 --> 03:38.426
-You'll never guess where I found it.
-I never will.

03:39.719 --> 03:44.390
Look, you and I
have hung out a lot today.

03:44.557 --> 03:46.476
-Yeah.
-So, uh....

03:50.896 --> 03:53.023
-Can I finish my beer?
-How much is left?

03:55.109 --> 03:56.569
[BEER SLOSHING FAINTLY]

03:56.736 --> 03:58.779
It's, like, less than half.

03:59.364 --> 04:00.865
Fine.

04:02.450 --> 04:05.786
Hey, Jeff, uh, I'm on hold
with the people from that Pilates studio.

04:05.953 --> 04:08.831
They say I'm not signed up for my
class. You mailed that check, right?

04:08.998 --> 04:11.792
Oh. No. I'm sorry.
It's right over here.

04:11.959 --> 04:16.922
Well, how could you forget that?
It was weeks ago.

04:17.214 --> 04:18.549
Yeah, I'm still here.

04:18.716 --> 04:21.218
Um, I owe you an apology.

04:21.386 --> 04:23.804
Oh, man, looks like
doghouse city for you.

04:23.971 --> 04:26.474
-Oh, I'm gonna be fine.
-How do you figure, man?

04:26.641 --> 04:28.142
Audrey had the same look Jen had...

04:28.309 --> 04:31.061
...when she found my rollerblade
in her bubble bath.

04:32.938 --> 04:34.732
See, whenever Aud screws up...

04:34.899 --> 04:37.902
...instead of getting mad
and shoving it in her face...

04:38.068 --> 04:40.946
...I just deposit it into this handy file.

04:41.113 --> 04:42.823
The bank.

04:43.991 --> 04:45.493
-The bank?
-Tsk.

04:45.660 --> 04:47.662
That's right.
Then when I screw up...

04:47.828 --> 04:52.958
...I withdraw one of her old screw-ups
to neutralize her anger.

04:53.543 --> 04:55.503
Seems kind of petty and manipulative.

04:55.670 --> 04:57.254
Thanks.

04:58.548 --> 05:00.341
Great, you didn't mail that check...

05:00.508 --> 05:02.968
...and now there are no more spots
left in the class.

05:03.135 --> 05:06.722
Never forget to mail a check
to the beer of the month club, do you?

05:06.889 --> 05:09.892
First of all,
I have that on autopay, and....

05:10.726 --> 05:13.563
You know, I said I was sorry.
And people forget things.

05:13.729 --> 05:17.692
I mean, just by way of random example,
uh, a few weeks ago...

05:17.858 --> 05:20.486
...uh, you forgot to return
that Mamma Mia! DVD.

05:21.278 --> 05:24.574
And by the time we found it
in the couch cushions, we owned it.

05:25.366 --> 05:27.076
For 80 bucks.

05:27.577 --> 05:30.413
-Well, that was--
-A similar incident? Sure.

05:30.580 --> 05:35.084
But I only bring it up
to show that people aren't perfect.

05:36.377 --> 05:37.420
Well, that's true.

05:37.587 --> 05:40.214
I don't think I even got mad at you.

05:41.841 --> 05:44.677
No, you were actually
pretty understanding.

05:44.844 --> 05:49.890
So I guess this is,
like, a teachable moment.

05:52.643 --> 05:54.979
You're right. I'm sorry I got upset.

05:56.772 --> 05:58.023
[MOUTHS]
Wow.

06:00.359 --> 06:01.569
Apology accepted.

06:01.736 --> 06:05.072
I'm going to the dry cleaners.
Want me to pick you up a pizza?

06:05.239 --> 06:08.158
I'll end the suspense. Yes.

06:09.494 --> 06:11.036
Bye.

06:14.206 --> 06:17.126
She stopped being mad,
and she's gonna get you a pizza?

06:18.711 --> 06:21.506
Thank you for banking with us,
Mr. Bingham.

06:22.882 --> 06:24.884
Oh, man, I gotta try this with Jen.

06:25.050 --> 06:27.637
Well, I'm glad I could help.
Anyways, um....

06:30.055 --> 06:32.767
I think we both know
what this means.

06:33.267 --> 06:34.644
[♪♪♪]

06:36.604 --> 06:39.524
Ah, good morning, my paid friend.

06:40.357 --> 06:43.778
Yes, I'll just note that 2:15
is now part of the morning.

06:44.945 --> 06:47.072
So make any progress with Allison?

06:47.239 --> 06:48.282
Hmm?

06:48.449 --> 06:51.786
She give you a shout-out
on the old email machine, hmm?

06:52.870 --> 06:54.789
-No.
-Really?

06:55.665 --> 07:00.711
Yes. And before you tell me to
notch up the offensive or step into it...

07:00.878 --> 07:03.631
...or put something on a rag
and make her smell it...

07:05.841 --> 07:08.010
...I've got it under control.

07:08.177 --> 07:11.388
Oh, fine.
Far be it from me to get involved.

07:11.556 --> 07:14.391
Yes, it be far.

07:15.976 --> 07:19.439
-Well, I'm gonna take a little break.
-You've certainly earned it.

07:21.065 --> 07:24.109
Make sure you're back by 3:10
or you'll miss quitting time.

07:35.663 --> 07:37.206
Oh, hey there.

07:37.372 --> 07:38.541
Allison is it?

07:38.708 --> 07:40.793
Uh, right. Hello, Mr. Dunbar.

07:40.960 --> 07:42.002
Hey there.

07:42.169 --> 07:45.172
I don't think I've given you my official
welcome to the company, heh.

07:46.048 --> 07:48.175
I have mace, heh.

07:48.676 --> 07:49.885
Jeez, relax.

07:50.052 --> 07:52.847
Sorry.
It's just, I've heard some stories.

07:53.514 --> 07:56.183
Oh, yeah? Well, some of them
are probably exaggerated...

07:56.350 --> 07:57.477
...heh, for all you know.

07:58.686 --> 08:01.230
-So having a little tea? Heh.
-Yes.

08:01.396 --> 08:06.486
You know, speaking of tea, uh, it usually
comes from faraway places, like Asia...

08:06.652 --> 08:09.321
...and darker in color
than, say, milk.

08:09.489 --> 08:11.406
You know my assistant, Timmy,
right?

08:12.449 --> 08:13.868
I'm familiar with his work.

08:14.034 --> 08:18.122
I think he likes you, heh.
OMG alert.

08:18.873 --> 08:21.458
Yes, he's made that
abundantly clear.

08:21.626 --> 08:22.793
Ah.

08:22.960 --> 08:25.170
Well, do you like him?

08:25.337 --> 08:26.338
[CHUCKLES]

08:26.506 --> 08:30.259
I mean, I know he's no Tom Cruise.
I mean, we know, heh.

08:30.425 --> 08:34.722
He's got the goofy specs, built
like Mr. Salty, but he's a sweet kid.

08:34.889 --> 08:37.892
-Well, I thought so, but, uh--
-But what?

08:38.058 --> 08:40.352
Well, yesterday, he sent me this email...

08:40.520 --> 08:42.479
-...that was just so shocking.
-Ah.

08:42.647 --> 08:44.356
--ly good?

08:44.524 --> 08:46.025
--ly disgusting.

08:46.191 --> 08:49.612
Turns out he's a total pig.
And an idiot.

08:50.821 --> 08:52.740
Why is he an idiot?

08:53.282 --> 08:56.410
Well, to start, he spelled "straddle"
with Ts instead of Ds.

08:56.994 --> 08:58.704
It's Ds?

08:58.871 --> 09:01.749
It was like being sexually harassed
by a fourth grader.

09:02.875 --> 09:05.377
Well, maybe when he was a kid
he was dyslexic.

09:05.545 --> 09:08.422
But his parents didn't notice
because they were too busy...

09:08.589 --> 09:11.300
...self-medicating
with gin and cough syrup.

09:11.466 --> 09:15.888
Using their friends as pawns
in their games of sexual chess.

09:16.556 --> 09:18.766
Well, that might excuse
his near-literacy.

09:21.101 --> 09:22.477
With that ugly attitude...

09:22.645 --> 09:25.606
...he'll never have any sort
of meaningful relationship.

09:27.733 --> 09:31.028
Sorry. I guess those are tough words
to hear about your friend.

09:31.528 --> 09:32.988
Yeah, my friend.

09:35.449 --> 09:37.451
[♪♪♪]

09:39.411 --> 09:41.121
Hey, hon, back from the store.

09:41.288 --> 09:43.958
Oh, great, just in time.
Let me have the milk.

09:44.374 --> 09:46.085
Oh, yeah.

09:46.752 --> 09:50.130
You forgot the milk? I just
reminded you, like, 15 minutes ago.

09:50.297 --> 09:52.466
It was the one thing I asked for.

09:53.008 --> 09:55.761
Oh, yeah? Well....

09:56.178 --> 09:57.847
How about the time
we were broken up...

09:58.013 --> 10:00.432
...and you had sex
with your ex-boyfriend, huh?

10:01.266 --> 10:03.853
What?
Did you actually just say that?

10:04.478 --> 10:06.021
Yeah.

10:06.521 --> 10:08.608
It shows that we all make mistakes.

10:10.359 --> 10:12.778
This isn't a teachable moment, is it?

10:14.571 --> 10:15.615
[SHOWER RUNNING]

10:15.781 --> 10:19.660
JEFF:
♪ We are the champions ♪

10:19.827 --> 10:25.916
♪ We are the champions
No time for losers ♪

10:26.083 --> 10:29.629
♪ Because we are the champions ♪

10:32.673 --> 10:34.133
♪ Of the world ♪♪

10:34.299 --> 10:35.718
Jeff.

10:36.135 --> 10:37.720
Yeah?

10:39.764 --> 10:43.558
-Want in on this?
-No, I'm good. I was on the computer...

10:43.726 --> 10:47.021
...trying to cancel the check I wrote
for that Pilates class...

10:47.187 --> 10:50.107
...when I came upon a little file
called Bank.

10:51.316 --> 10:53.653
-Did you?
-Yeah.

10:54.444 --> 10:57.114
Still feel like the champion
of the world?

10:57.406 --> 10:59.408
[♪♪♪]

11:01.201 --> 11:03.203
[♪♪♪]

11:04.329 --> 11:05.455
A file?

11:05.622 --> 11:09.251
You keep a file of every mistake
I have made over the years?

11:09.418 --> 11:11.837
I'm sure I've missed a few.
I'm not perfect.

11:12.504 --> 11:13.672
Oh, my God.

11:13.839 --> 11:17.134
Every time when you were
so understanding, it was just a ploy.

11:17.301 --> 11:20.637
I learned early that if you
screwed up and I called you on it...

11:20.805 --> 11:23.891
...you'd just get madder at me.
I'd get nothing out of it.

11:24.767 --> 11:26.977
Why do you have to get something
out of it?

11:27.144 --> 11:29.604
Why can't you just be
kind and understanding?

11:29.772 --> 11:33.358
That would be fine in a world of fairies
and magic bunnies.

11:34.777 --> 11:36.695
This is marriage we're talking about.

11:36.862 --> 11:39.949
It's a constant series of battles
to be won and lost.

11:40.115 --> 11:43.452
How would you feel
if I stored up your screw-ups, huh?

11:43.618 --> 11:46.205
Like when you forgot to pick me up
at the airport.

11:46.371 --> 11:49.499
Or that time you forgot your credit card
at the strip club.

11:49.666 --> 11:54.379
Tsk, well, I mean, first of all, those are
technically part of the same incident.

11:54.546 --> 11:59.468
And, uh, secondly, it sounds to me
like you do store those up.

11:59.634 --> 12:04.098
No, I just happen to remember them.
I don't log them into my hard drive.

12:04.264 --> 12:05.432
Enjoy the guest room.

12:05.599 --> 12:09.353
You're the one telling me I should
write stuff down so I don't forget.

12:09.519 --> 12:11.271
You should be proud of me!

12:11.856 --> 12:12.898
[DOOR SLAMS]

12:13.065 --> 12:14.233
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

12:22.783 --> 12:24.618
I think my bank needs a bailout.

12:25.452 --> 12:27.454
[♪♪♪]

12:29.331 --> 12:33.585
You sent this email to a woman,
an actual human woman?

12:34.586 --> 12:35.670
Yeah, dude.

12:35.838 --> 12:38.007
-That always works for me.
JEFF: Oh, really?

12:38.173 --> 12:41.385
"I want to lick vanilla icing
off your lady bumps."

12:43.220 --> 12:46.390
That stuff only works on
your particular brand of skank.

12:47.599 --> 12:51.353
Don't think you can play cupid
just because you're the same height.

12:53.022 --> 12:55.190
I'm sorry,
is this coming from two guys...

12:55.357 --> 12:57.442
...who spent last night
spooning on a couch...

12:57.609 --> 12:59.778
...because their chicks
gave them the boot?

12:59.945 --> 13:01.321
We were not spooning.

13:01.488 --> 13:03.657
Jeff was in the guest room
and I was on the couch.

13:03.824 --> 13:07.786
-Till about 4:00 a.m.
-I heard a noise! I got scared!

13:08.370 --> 13:09.413
So sad.

13:09.955 --> 13:11.331
Good day there, gents.

13:11.498 --> 13:13.125
RUSSELL: Hey.
-Hmm? What's that?

13:13.292 --> 13:14.626
"Please join us for breakfast."

13:14.793 --> 13:17.296
Thanks ever so much for asking,
but I can't.

13:17.462 --> 13:19.214
You see, this is the morning...

13:19.381 --> 13:21.633
...I make my move
on the enchanting Allison.

13:21.800 --> 13:22.843
Mm-hm.

13:23.010 --> 13:26.889
How? What, do you visit the father's
hut, swing a chicken around?

13:29.349 --> 13:31.685
No. I am bringing her something...

13:31.852 --> 13:33.854
...that comes close
to matching her in sweetness.

13:34.646 --> 13:35.898
A cupcake.

13:36.065 --> 13:38.567
-Uh, chocolate?
-Vanilla.

13:41.820 --> 13:43.072
Well then, wish me luck.

13:44.114 --> 13:47.701
Hmm? No? Nothing? That's fine.
Silent prayers then.

13:49.203 --> 13:51.663
Heh, dude,
he got her a vanilla cupcake.

13:51.830 --> 13:53.457
It's too perfect.

13:53.623 --> 13:56.001
No, it's not perfect, man.
You gotta stop him.

13:56.168 --> 14:00.214
-Yeah, he's walking into a buzz saw.
-All right, you guys are probably right.

14:00.380 --> 14:02.757
This could be
the most humiliating experience.

14:02.925 --> 14:04.551
I should stop it. I'm responsible.

14:04.718 --> 14:07.387
I gotta be the one-- Yay. Pancakes!

14:07.596 --> 14:09.181
[♪♪♪]

14:09.389 --> 14:10.640
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

14:12.059 --> 14:14.061
-Knock, knock.
-Timmy.

14:16.230 --> 14:18.773
I bring sweets for the sweet.

14:18.941 --> 14:19.942
Oh.

14:20.109 --> 14:23.695
I thought if I ignored you, you'd get
the message, but apparently not.

14:28.575 --> 14:30.953
-Have I done something to offend you?
-Really?

14:31.120 --> 14:35.582
You have no idea about the poem
you emailed me titled Points of Entry?

14:37.126 --> 14:40.712
-Allison, I didn't send you any email.
-Then what's this?

14:40.880 --> 14:42.297
[TYPING]

14:43.507 --> 14:45.467
-Mr. Dunbar.
-What about him?

14:45.634 --> 14:47.177
He sent that.

14:48.053 --> 14:50.347
-You have to believe me.
-Why should I?

14:50.805 --> 14:53.017
Allison,
I was first in my class at Oxford.

14:53.183 --> 14:56.645
Do you really think I'd spell "pelvis"
with two Ls?

14:57.396 --> 15:01.108
I guess not. And I did think it was odd
that you misspelled "finish."

15:01.275 --> 15:02.776
No, that's actually correct.

15:02.943 --> 15:06.613
It refers to an apparatus
he ordered from Finland.

15:06.780 --> 15:08.908
But I assure you,
I would never disrespect you...

15:09.074 --> 15:11.743
...or any other woman
with this kind of language.

15:11.911 --> 15:14.663
It's such a relief to know that
you're still the charming gentleman...

15:14.829 --> 15:16.623
...I thought you were.

15:16.916 --> 15:19.876
And an even greater relief
to hear you call me charming.

15:20.044 --> 15:23.213
You are, heh. I mean, you're certainly
not the kind of person...

15:23.380 --> 15:26.050
...that would want to watch me
do this, heh.

15:26.216 --> 15:28.385
With a jar of that.

15:29.678 --> 15:31.596
Ahem, goodness no. Um....

15:32.597 --> 15:37.227
And I'm certainly far too refined
to even suggest that we try that.

15:38.312 --> 15:39.521
How can you do that?

15:39.688 --> 15:42.399
That's what the Helsinki harness
is for.

15:43.733 --> 15:46.861
But if we were to complete that act...

15:47.029 --> 15:51.741
...one can see how it would segue
very nicely into, uh....

15:51.992 --> 15:54.828
Oh, into that right there in all caps.

15:56.913 --> 16:00.625
It all seems so forbidden
and naughty.

16:01.668 --> 16:03.837
Naughty indeed.

16:17.934 --> 16:19.436
[ALLISON GASPS]

16:19.644 --> 16:20.687
[♪♪♪]

16:24.274 --> 16:25.317
Hey, honey.

16:25.484 --> 16:26.526
[DOOR CLOSES]

16:26.693 --> 16:28.820
Hooray. You're here.

16:29.529 --> 16:32.116
Look, I feel really bad
about last night.

16:32.282 --> 16:36.120
So I brought you a little something.

16:37.246 --> 16:38.622
That's cute.

16:38.788 --> 16:41.708
Okay, look, I know this doesn't
make up for what I said.

16:41.875 --> 16:45.712
But I thought it might get us
2 percent closer.

16:46.463 --> 16:47.506
[CHUCKLES]

16:47.672 --> 16:48.923
You're such a dork.

16:50.217 --> 16:52.177
I'm really sorry.

16:52.344 --> 16:54.429
It was just so harsh
and out of nowhere.

16:54.596 --> 16:59.809
-I know. I mean, see, Jeff said--
-My God, I knew this smelled like him.

16:59.976 --> 17:03.230
You know, lately
so does the elevator.

17:03.397 --> 17:06.941
-We don't need his relationship tricks.
-I know, and to be honest...

17:07.109 --> 17:10.070
...I'm not upset you slept
with Serge when we broke up.

17:10.237 --> 17:13.740
-Well, you shouldn't be.
-And I have got no right to complain...

17:13.907 --> 17:18.120
...because that week
I slept with my ex and her friend, heh.

17:20.580 --> 17:23.958
Oh, look, we have another carton
right here in the door.

17:24.376 --> 17:25.794
Brain fart.

17:26.545 --> 17:27.587
[♪♪♪]

17:30.632 --> 17:35.054
Oh, I'd like the apartment to be bigger
too but I don't think that's gonna do it.

17:37.013 --> 17:40.267
I'm stretching. Something
I was hoping to do in Pilates.

17:40.434 --> 17:42.436
Speaking of which.

17:44.771 --> 17:46.898
-You got me into the class?
-I did.

17:47.066 --> 17:50.735
It was totally full. How'd you do that?
Know anything about scoliosis?

17:50.902 --> 17:52.237
No.

17:52.404 --> 17:55.574
Well, read up, because the Pilates
people think you have it.

17:57.201 --> 18:00.787
Are you still mad about....

18:01.371 --> 18:02.664
No, I'm not mad.

18:02.831 --> 18:04.874
I'm just disappointed.

18:05.041 --> 18:07.836
I don't want to be a couple
who fights like that...

18:08.002 --> 18:10.839
...all calculating, storing stuff up,
using it later.

18:11.005 --> 18:13.007
Tell you what, how about
from now on--

18:13.175 --> 18:15.219
Oh, I agree, no more fighting.

18:15.385 --> 18:17.637
Well, that's a little pie
in the sky. Uh....

18:18.180 --> 18:19.598
I was gonna say...

18:19.764 --> 18:22.851
...how about we just fight about
what we're fighting about at the time.

18:23.017 --> 18:24.144
Okay.

18:24.311 --> 18:26.188
Let's start by deleting the bank.

18:26.355 --> 18:28.815
All right, and I'll get rid of this too.

18:29.858 --> 18:31.818
[JEFF SIGHS]

18:32.944 --> 18:33.987
[THUMP]

18:37.449 --> 18:39.075
You printed it out?

18:39.243 --> 18:41.453
You gotta have backup
of all your important files.

18:41.620 --> 18:45.415
Let's just say that the computer
crashes, what, are we gonna not fight?

18:47.251 --> 18:52.297
Oh, you've been saving this stuff up
since I spilled gravy on your tuxedo?

18:52.881 --> 18:55.509
I wasn't gonna yell at you
on our wedding day.

18:58.387 --> 19:02.098
August '98, dropped new camera
into the Grand Canyon.

19:02.266 --> 19:06.228
You wouldn't wear the strap because
it clashed with your stupid purse.

19:06.686 --> 19:08.522
Is what I didn't say at the time.

19:11.858 --> 19:17.239
June '06, paid for insurance on rental
car when credit card covered anyway.

19:17.406 --> 19:21.701
January '09, asked for a bite
of my sandwich, took three.

19:24.829 --> 19:26.080
Wow.

19:26.248 --> 19:29.959
-Ha, ha, we have had some good times.
-Yes, we have.

19:30.835 --> 19:32.629
You know,
maybe we shouldn't destroy this.

19:32.796 --> 19:34.088
No?

19:34.256 --> 19:37.926
-I mean, we don't take a lot of pictures.
-Camera. Grand Canyon.

19:39.969 --> 19:41.012
Right.

19:41.180 --> 19:44.599
It's pretty much
the, uh, only record of our life together.

19:44.766 --> 19:46.768
-A scrapbook of our marriage.
-Heh.

19:46.935 --> 19:49.396
Or evidence for our divorce.

19:50.647 --> 19:53.983
Who knows where
this crazy ride's gonna take us.

19:54.150 --> 19:55.151
[CHUCKLES]

19:58.280 --> 20:03.034
Hey, I, uh, recorded Gran Torino in
the bedroom. You want to go watch it?

20:03.202 --> 20:04.911
Yeah, sure.

20:05.287 --> 20:06.330
Oh.

20:06.496 --> 20:09.082
Um, I think my Oprahs
bumped it off the TiVo.

20:09.541 --> 20:12.126
No problem.
Uh, we'll watch something else.

20:12.294 --> 20:13.503
-Hmm.
-I'll be right in.

20:13.670 --> 20:15.630
-I'm gonna get some chips.
-Okay.

20:15.797 --> 20:17.382
[SIGHS]

20:22.637 --> 20:24.639
[♪♪♪]

20:28.059 --> 20:29.519
[♪♪♪]

20:29.686 --> 20:34.483
The Office Depot people never let
on quite how versatile this baby was.

20:35.024 --> 20:38.695
When they called it a five-position
chair, I think they missed a few.

20:38.862 --> 20:41.448
Oh, now, I think it's for the best...

20:41.615 --> 20:43.867
...if Mr. Dunbar never learns
of the role he played...

20:44.033 --> 20:46.495
...in prompting
this most recent activity.

20:46.661 --> 20:48.913
We wouldn't want to encourage
his involvement in our affairs.

20:49.080 --> 20:50.332
Agreed.

20:50.499 --> 20:53.126
In fact, let's just delete that email
right now.

20:53.293 --> 20:54.919
Good idea.

20:55.920 --> 20:58.047
Oh, and Allison.

20:58.798 --> 21:00.300
Print out a copy first?

21:00.842 --> 21:02.093
You read my mind.

21:02.302 --> 21:04.304
[♪♪♪]

21:08.517 --> 21:10.519
[♪♪♪]
